Edit:  Can't find the numbers but the largest creditors seem to be the Gulf States (which? - probably Kuwait since 199 billion -over half- of the debt is reparations), Japan, France, Germany, and Russia.  So, Tangurena may have a darn fine point. An interesting topic to look into for us.  I would like to think that the USA is bigger than only doing this in order to flip the bird to the world.
