Now, what to do?  Does the new Iraq simply refuse to pay?  Do creditors sell the debt (is there a market for such a huge debt)?  Does the USA somehow convince the creditors to forgive part of the debt?  Does the USA tell the creditors to accept what the new the deal or get nothing?  Are only the loans after 1991 forgiven because Hussein was our buddy before then? If the creditors are forced to accept the deal or forgive loans what does this do to the ability of Iraq to borrow money from anyone but the USA for reconstruction and defense?  Can the USA afford to float loans to Iraq, when no one else will?  Lots of interesting questions.<span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Elberich V2.0 on Sun Oct 19, 2003 3:21 pm; edited 3 times in total</span>


