			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><div class="postbody">One of the major financial reasons for going into war so soon was that Iraq was pushing to change the standard for barrels of oil from dollars to the euro.
<br />

<br />
This change would have had a profound effect on the dollar, effectively removing it as the main currency worldwide and replacing it with the euro.
<br />

<br />
The value of the dollar would have been severely harmed as a result.  The buying power of the dollar would have fallen dramatically, making any goods we import more expensive.
<br />

<br />
In essence, that change would have caused a shitstorm in the US economy which has long relied upon the relative stability of the dollar.
<br />

<br />
What Hussein wanted to do was not illegal by any means, so our government had to produce other reasons to attack him.  Letting him think he could invade Kawait was the first step.  Once he did that, we could place sanctions on him and prevent the conversion from taking place.
<br />

<br />
After over a decade, pressure was building in the UN to eventually lift sanctions, which would then have allowed Hussein to continue with his plans.  Thus the only solution for the US govt would be to paint him as an imminent threat and remove him from power permanently.
<br />

<br />
9/11 became the perfect excuse for this action.  By convincing that public that Iraq had ties to terrorist organizations, the US government was able to get Congress to quickly approve a preemptive strike on Iraq.
<br />

<br />
Even though the UN didn't approve the attack, no countries could risk a military confrontation with the US to try and stop it.  Unfortunately the costs of invading without a broad coalition have become staggering.   
<br />

<br />
Congress knows it will have to answer for the costs come election time.  So they have voted to make a large portion a loan to cushion the damage the costs will do to their re-election efforts.   They don't have Iraq's stability at heart, but rather's their careers'.<span class="gensmall"></span>


				</div></td>
			</tr>
