			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><div class="postbody">CNN was the most centrist source I could find regarding Iraq's intentions for the dollar to euro conversion for oil:
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.cnn.com/2000/WORLD/meast/10/30/iraq.un.euro.reut/" target="_blank">http://www.cnn.com/2000/WORLD/meast/10/30/iraq.un.euro.reut/</a>
<br />

<br />
Numerous sites explain in more detail what I mentioned, most are leftist publications.  This link is mostly for providing financial info on the damage the US economy would suffer if Iraq and OPEC sold oil for euros instead of dollars:
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.andrew.h.lohmann.btinternet.co.uk/dollars_euros_and_war_in_iraq.html" target="_blank">http://www.andrew.h.lohmann.btinternet.co.uk/dollars_euros_and_war_in_iraq.html</a>
<br />

<br />
Here's another tidbit of info, this time regarding Venezuela (another oil producing country) and it's intentions of moving from dollars to euros:
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.globalpolicy.org/nations/sovereign/dollar/2003/0624euro.htm" target="_blank">http://www.globalpolicy.org/nations/sovereign/dollar/2003/0624euro.htm</a>
<br />

<br />
Essentially if oil producing countries as a whole switched from selling oil for euros instead of dollars, the dollar would be severely weakened.  In addition, the reserves of dollars held by foreign counties would no longer be needed.  As a result, the US would have to start paying back it's debt (aka deficit) to other countries as those reserves were depleted.
<br />

<br />
Here's another interesting commentary I found that details how and why the US economy relies so heavily on foreign countries maintaining reserves of dollars:
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.scoop.co.nz/mason/stories/HL0310/S00140.htm" target="_blank">http://www.scoop.co.nz/mason/stories/HL0310/S00140.htm</a>
<br />

<br />
Given the economic threat, you might find it surprising that US officials have made no mention of it as a justification for war.   However, as I mentioned before, US citizens have no stomach for a war based on purely financial reasons.  Send your sons and daughters in harm's way to keep the US dollar and economy strong?  Naw, that wouldn't fly would it?<span class="gensmall"></span>


