Being a good capitalist, I think a nation should be free to conduct business in its own products with who they want and how they want - including Iraqi oil. The market should be allowed freedom.  If consumers disagree with the way a commodity market is being handled we need to find alternatives.  That way the market will change to reflect the value consumers put on a commodity or lose its market.  The consumer will go elswhere - if they have the balls to find an alternative rather than being lead around by a nose ring held by the Middle East.<span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Elberich V2.0 on Mon Oct 20, 2003 5:59 pm; edited 3 times in total</span>


